WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:10.160 --> 00:00:16.260
I've really enjoyed the initial presentation
and the fact that we should be focusing on

00:00:16.260 --> 00:00:21.460
health care as well as cost, and the big emphasis
on data I think is really important because

00:00:21.460 --> 00:00:27.409
without data you can't really get any information
or be able to make any positive change.

00:00:27.409 --> 00:00:31.470
There's a really big field of people that
have come in for it, both presenters and attendees,

00:00:31.470 --> 00:00:36.230
and I think there's always such a fertile
seedbed for ideas and for networking and the

00:00:36.230 --> 00:00:39.070
great things that we can all take back to
our LHDs.

00:00:39.070 --> 00:00:45.260
It's been a fantastic conference so far, so
many excellent speakers and really amazing

00:00:45.260 --> 00:00:47.699
international presentations.

00:00:47.699 --> 00:00:52.660
Well I think it's been very encouraging that
the outlook is always in relation to the patient,

00:00:52.660 --> 00:00:57.550
the outcome of the patients, and I think probably
years from now that's going to be the main

00:00:57.550 --> 00:00:59.579
driver for any health innovations.

00:00:59.579 --> 00:01:05.230
I think the biggest highlight is just the
validation that Australia and America are

00:01:05.230 --> 00:01:11.690
working on the same problems in the same ways
and really trying to come up with collective

00:01:11.690 --> 00:01:16.820
solutions that are going to improve the outcome
of the care delivery to cancer patients.

00:01:16.820 --> 00:01:22.230
There's a lot old friends here as well as
new colleagues to meet and just to hear that

00:01:22.230 --> 00:01:28.240
innovations in cancer are continuing to be
made, so there's new content every time I

00:01:28.240 --> 00:01:29.600
come along to the conference.

00:01:29.600 --> 00:01:34.150
I think it's sharing ideas with all the people
who are doing great work across NSW.

00:01:34.150 --> 00:01:40.630
I think it brings innovation managers and
staff and administrators and lots of different

00:01:40.630 --> 00:01:41.700
people together to talk.

00:01:41.700 --> 00:01:48.930
This is my third year now and it's very interesting
to see how advances in technology seem to

00:01:48.930 --> 00:01:52.310
be driving a lot of the discussion we're having
today.

